# Build artifacts
target/
pkgconfig/

# Deliberately NOT ignored: output/tectonic_wasm.wasm (3.3 MB).
#
# It looks like a build output, but right now it cannot be rebuilt: the link
# step fails on any current toolchain (see BACKLOG.md #1), so this binary is a
# fossil of the exact toolchain nl5887 used. Untracked, a single `git clean
# -xfd` would destroy it permanently and we could not produce another.
#
# It does NOT validate the current source: it exports the old `tectonic_*` ABI,
# not our `glyphx_*` one, so the e2e suite cannot run against it. What it is
# good for is proving the toolchain target is reachable at all, and pinning the
# import surface — its 24 imports are what packages/tex-engine/src/imports.ts
# is written against, and they match.
#
# Re-add `output/*.wasm` here once scripts/build-wasm.sh links successfully —
# at that point it becomes reproducible, and tracking it would only add
# megabytes of churn to every commit.

# Deliberately NOT ignored: output/tectonic-bundle.tar.gz and output/latex.fmt.
#
# Those are data inputs, not build outputs — they come from a TeX Live install
# and cannot be regenerated without one, so dropping them would leave the repo
# unbuildable and untestable on a clean machine. They are also stable, changing
# only when the TeX Live snapshot is refreshed, so they cost history size once
# rather than continuously.

# OS
.DS_Store
*.swp
*~
